<br>
    While hunting Scarlet Desert I decided I wanted to get the Katta Enduring breath necklace.  The Scarlet Desert side of the Grey didn't look too promising so I made my way to the Mons Letalis zone side.  Learned a couple things along the way.  Nothing I encountered sees through invisibility.  Shiny spots are the ground are either worms or triggers to spawn them, fortunately they didn't see through invisibility.<br>
     Found lots of Shissar Stalkers out from Mons Letalis Zone behind two lines of Timeless Golems and Shimmering Rockfiends.  Testing the 51 earth pet I pulled a couple of the golems and rockfiends.  Good experience, but no real loot couple opals so not horrible.  But I came for the Shissar Guts.  Too bad...every time I pulled a Shissar a Golem would come even though it was quite a ways away.<br>
     First time it happened I sacrificed the pet and ran for the zone.  Fortunately nothing paths near the zone.  On the other side was quite a shock.  Bodies were every where.  I went out side the tunnel and saw a stream of Mature Rockhoppers about 45 seconds apart pathing up the wall just east of the zone tunnel.  Back inside at the Grey Zone I summoned another pet kit and a few more water stones and medded to full unmolested.  I did this several more times and was never jumped by anything.  While the experience was very good I never got a single Shissar to pull.  <br>
     Research led me to Taskmaster Torkazh.  He is in Echo Caverns and surrounded by undead slaves.  I was KOS to him and apprehensive to the slaves.  He conned blue and so did the slaves with the rare exceptional light blue.  The slaves will assist the Taskmaster once he is in combat so you have to pull down the tunnel and he is very fast.  Since the Taskmaster is on a 20 minute timer I petted up and pulled immediately.  Malaised and 4 lavabolts later the pet was at 30 and I was disappointed that no guts dropped.  I killed the next 20 mins pulling up the pet kit, killing the slaves and the underbulks and fungusfiends from the room below (Lightblue but better loot, skellys have no loot but so so exp)<br>
    Xilniov eventually spawned and conned yellow.  I camped.  Two hours later when I logged back on he was gone and the room was still available.  All total I had about 3 hours invested to get the three guts I needed and made 4 blues and about 70 pp (Off of the lower room)<br>
    Heheheh since I got the necklace I've been exploring Kedge Keep and have all intentions of returning to the Grey.  For solo I liked it better than Scarlet Desert plus there are a lot of mobs right there by the zone.  I know waterstones are  a pain but after you have the eb necklace you won't care.  Been trying to get friends and guild members to go out there with me....fear is a terrible thing  *<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
